name: Kashif Abdul Razzaq Misidia
text:
Wonderful experience at Masala Art. After a long time I can say, I eat an authentic Barbecue here.
We are Barbecue lovers, and often tried Barbecue restaurants in Karachi. But this place was something different.
We ordered a new arrival Tangri Kabab here, along with Beef Bihari boti which we tried at many places. But here we found a different taste. Especially Tangri Kabab was meat of Chicken leg, and it was juicy with tasty spices. Prices here are very reasonable and the best thing about this place is ♿ Accessible for Wheelchairs and for the people with different abilities.

name: Ghayyur Tirmazi (Techno Solar Pakistan)
text:
While in Karachi & staying in Gulshan Area, one can't skip visiting Hassan Square Food Street. A lot of hotels, vendors are there with variety of dishes. Fried fish is every where but Sajji is also as famous as fish.

Mehran Sajji is situated along with a couple of other Sajji houses like Quetta Sajji & Bolan Sajji. The competition among them seems to be huge so I'm sure taste quality of all of them should also be great.

Both Mehran & Quetta Sajji have outside seating but Bolan are for gentry, air conditioned halls and besides Sajji they offer other dished also. They are night time hotels & sizeable customers are present there for enjoying their dishes.

name: Ali Haider
text:
This place is so underrated in my opinion. I had their Paneer Reshmi Handi and Mutton Karahi and both of them were prepared with hygiene and safety.

What I loved about their Paneer Reshmi is the fact that it was oozing with creamy cheesy flavors. It was delicious and cooked to perfection.

Mutton Karahi was a delicious as well and the meat was tender.

I'd give them 5/5 stars for taste and hygiene and reasonable prices.

name: Adeel Zaidi
text: I wish I could give this location less then 1 star. We were there Thursday night with majority of the hall unoccupied. We were there with family friends for dinner at the entrance gentleman was very nice and had us go upstairs to check out family hall before making our decision because we were concerned about how busy they looked. Hall was very congested but we still decided to eat there and that’s where the nightmare started. Food was ok however service was HORRIBLE we had no silverware to eat with, 3 items that we ordered had no spoons in it that could be used to take out the hot gravy from the clay pot. After asking few times for silverware and napkins we were presented with silverware but no napkins. I walked up to the main desk and asked for the items needed and placed order for some extra Naans and Paratha which were never delivered upon asking for them again I was told it will take 20 mins for naans and 25 mins for paratha. Being super disappointed we ate what we had and waited for the bill. Our host had to walk up to the front counter to ask for it and was told that they will bring it in few minutes. Me the guest was presented with the receipt/bill that one of the employee pulled out of his pocket, leaving me shocked and our host embarrassed. When we asked for management, answer was simple that “No one is available.”

I would recommend this place for it's food. The only advise would be don't take females with you if you are going for a dine-in. name: mohsin bhatti
text:
For me, it was an experience.

I wanted to try South Indian style food.

The ambience was generic nothing new and posh but acceptable if you are more into food than the location this is going to be a no big deal.

Originally born and bred in Lahore so oily and heavy food is no big deal. But South Indian food was super light and I didn't even knew I was full even up to my neck.

So I ordered a masala dosa and a mix thali.

I was served dosa first. The filing was potatoes and some other veggies and the spices were in an awesome balance. Too much gram masala mostly give me heartburn and this was not going to be, in this case of dosa.

I enjoyed the light crispy outside and mushy veggie filling, there was a curry and a chutney with it. Curry was just okay but the chutney. I never would have thought about coconut chutney until this day it was delightful I loved every last drop of it.

After dosa, they brought in the big thali. I don't know where to start this was exactly on my mind. So I tasted every single thing and each and everything was different in taste. My tongue was having a festival, at one moment I was happy and the next it was nostalgic sort of sad mixing up all the good childhood memories and how I remember different house hold handies which I had at different times in my life.

For me, it was an experience of different emotions. The food was good thou.

My second experience is not going to be based on emotions so I would rate the chicken dishes were the best than the dals and lastly the veggies. Lassi was pleasant and necessary to cut down all the gram Masala and spices. Rice and chapatis were there to fill the gut.

Will visit it again before leaving Karachi.
You should try it for once in your life just to experience the rich culture from south India.

name: Muhammad Hashir Fazal
text:
Tried out this Indian style thaali from D Thaliland in just Rs 450 with lassi, 2 chapati and papad. What else to ask for? Thaali consist of Daal, Mix Sabzi, Lokki, Butter Chicken, Green Chicken, Rice, Salad, Achar and Dokla ❤ It is all made by an aunty at home and sent to restaurant. Owner personally came and asked us if we liked it or not. To be honest you wont found it as something unique its ordinary ghar ka khana but truly something to try 
I will give it as 4
#follow #me on Instagram @myfoodietummy for more sizzling reviews ❤

name: Kashif Abdul Razzaq Misidia
text:
In a hectic traffic and super idiotic moving cars on the food street of hussainabad, there is this AMAZiNG EATERY called D'Thaliland!

Ordered
Mix thali and got pav bhaji free on bogo
Spicy chicken cheese dosa and got masla dosa free on bogo
Chickn malai roll
And pizza fries (complementary)

The thaaali was.... the most delicious food
It had achar, dhokla, salan, rice, daaal, sabzi, puri, lassi and pappad too 10/10
Pav bhaji ... 10/10
Dosa both 10/10

We ordered pizza fries but they were honest that the specific cheese that they put in it is not available, so i said " i came all the way from south region... and they tried to complement us with this beauty 8/10... ask me why 8... because those other bang on dishesssssss were a starrrrr...

The food was extremely fresh!

name: Taha Shahid
text: We heard about their good taste & servings. So me and my wife decided to visit this place on 16 Ramadan iftar. We really surprised that all good Google Maps reviews about this place are true. I always post honest reviews and I must say that you should visit at least once if you like cheesy fast food. Yes, food price is a little high but you will not regret it. Meet the Cheese restaurant is more expensive but it has worst service and taste. RHK served us free iftar platter which is a kind gesture. We ordered a large pizza, very tasty. A burger, again very tasty. A bucket of fries, crispy from outside soft from inside. Perfect! Also ordered a Pomo Berry drink which was so refreshing. All of it cost us PKR. 2800 for two of us. Absolutely fast and responsive service by the young staff. They had eyes on every table. Environment was cleaned and maintained. I tried to find some negative things but failed. Very happy! Alhamdulillah.

We truly understand how you are feeling at the moment. We also understand that due to expected high demand we were unable to give our top customer service.

We own our shortcomings and have already worked out on a plan to meet high demands.

If you are true food lover then we recommend you try out our food. Please share your number so we can get in touch with you. Kindly message us on our Instagram or Facebook page.

text: Next to dolmen mall Hydri, this restaurant is a hidden gem in the area serving southern cuisine. Pleasant sitting arrangement under pergola roof and patio chairs, the restaurant offers mostly Mexican dishes. The staff is very helpful and courteous , they were continuously reminding us to use masks and sanitizers. We ordered Chicken and beef streak with burgers and everything was awesome. Prices are on higher side, but food and arrangements justify it well. The place is good for groups and get togethers.

name: Shreen Khalid
responseFromOwnerText:
Assalam Ma'am. The review card left by Mr. Zohaib Khalid suggests that you liked the taste however felt that the quantity was less. Upon further investigation with your server Mr. Hanif, it has come to our attention that your table of four ordered 1 BLC and 1 Tenderstorm Steak which you felt was not enough. We would like to sincerely apologise for the misconception ma'am.

BLC is 300 grams of minced beef with 200 grams of cheese and a portion of 150 grams of fries and shredded beef along with sauces and sidelines. Normally it is enough for two people however everyone has a different appetite  and we would like to apologise that it was not enough for you and your friends.

Tenderstorm is a 400 to 450 grams of tenderloin steak along with once again 150 grams of fries and some sauces and sidelines. You are absolutely right that for the price you paid it should have been enough for your table. We will work on further improving ourselves according to customer feedback and would like to sincerely apologise that your experience with us was unsatisfactory.

However for the bulk of our customers it has been enough and is quite popular among them. Still we are very sorry that your experience with us was unsatisfactory.
text: No taste. No quantity. And extremely high prices.

text:
My worst ever experience, ambiance was good, server was over friendly as he saw three guys hanging around which is not professional as he asked us to keep our used forks (used for starters) in our hands while he bring main course.
Secondly the food was not value for money they put a lot of thoughts on menu but literally it was nothing like that, ordered some its raining chesse fries which was practically dry had to add chilli sauce just to swallow those, wings was good taramind wings.
As we were new to the place we asked whats good so the waiter replied BLC sir its too good when we saw it was 2k upon asking he said its one serving, and it have 3 type of chesse with minced beef that sounds good so he asked should i make it 3 and we decide to give a try by ordering one thankgod. That BLC came with good presentation when we tried it, it was pathetic like seriously if he had served that with some naan on charpai costing around 800rs that would be worth it but giving it fancy name and price tag of 2k definitely not worth the money. It was dry and i guess the restaurant was out of chesse the filling was just in between.
Well overall experience was not good at where almost 1.2k per person i would have done one good dinein and several food delivery which would have atleast some taste.

name: Maria Peati
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Ms. Maria,

Thank you for your response. We appreciate you taking time out and share your concerns with us.

Cheesy fries: As the name suggests these are fries with only cheese sauce. If you were looking for something with more flavor as we think majority of our customers prefer, please try IT'S RAINING CHEESE in your next visit.

Chicken Entree: Our fillets are served 80 ml of sauce approx which is usually enough for most customers however, we always provide extra sauce on customer's request. We are sorry if you did not get a chance to let our server's know during your visit or if they did not comply with your request. We would like to invite you again at a time of your convenience and contact our GM Mr. Amir Jamil before placing your order.

Paninis: Our Paninis are usually liked by our customers however it depends on customer's personal preference of flavours. We personally recommend you try Roasted Punch Panini (Chicken) if you prefer garlic mayo sauce or ,  Smokey Shredder Panini ( Shredded Beef) if you like a strong BBQ flavour.

We would love welcome you again and hope that our food will tantalize your taste buds.

name: Ali Asghar Arif
responseFromOwnerText:
Dear Sir,

We are extremely sorry to hear your review and it worries us that you had to face such a bad experience with us. We take our reviews very seriously and work towards continuous improvement.

We investigated your order and found out that our kitchen prepared your order in 11mins after order acceptance from Foodpanda, we waited for the FoodPanda rider. The rider collected your order with a delay of 10mins and then add the delivery time. This means your order was delivered with a delay and due to this reason your fries were soggy it wasn't worth the experience.

We always encourage dine-in experience as we are confident that we can change your reviews with our product.

We will truly appreciate if we can get your contact information to get in touch with you and specially invite you to have a meal with us.

We look forward to hear from you.

Regards,
Team Roadhouse Kitchen.

responseFromOwnerText: Thank you for your feedback. It is much appreciated. Hope to serve you again.
text:
We ordered :
Tamarind Wings
Cluck Pizza
Smokey Shredder Beef Burger
Cheese Stuffed Fried Chiecked fillet with Casablanca Souce
Coconut Ice cream
Total bille Rs2,550

Tamarind Wings were properly fried & juicy. These beauties came in metal bucket, with fries in bottom.
Taste 5/5
Quantity 5/5
Quality 5/5
Size 4/5

Cluck Pizza was a extra thin crust, it was crunchy. It was literally topped with yellow bell peppers which i have never seen at any restaurant which is located at this side of the bridge. It had amazing aroma of pure olive oil that i never experienced in Karachi. I asked the owner about this amazing olive aroma and he revealed their classical kitchen practices.
Taste 4/5
Size 4/5
Quality 5/5

Beef burger was messy&juicy, smoked shredded tender beef shredding was topped with their own made BBQ type sauce+cheese+onions(i think onions were caramelised). Fries were included
Taste 4/5
Size 5/5
Quality 5/5

Chicken fillet was filled with cheese. Deep fried with breadcrumbs.Came with veggies +fries topped with this orange Moroccan sauce. It was mild not that much spicy, cheese quantity inside was not that much. There were no choice in sidelines. I think i should have chosen grilled instead of fried fillet.
Taste 3/5
Size 5/5
Quality 5/5

Coconut ice cream was out of this world it was madeup of freshly harvested soft coconut meat/flesh. It was not hardened 'naariyal' or dried 'khopra'. It's purely made up with dairy& 'coconut malai'. Its a must try item of their menu. Usually air & oils or margrine is added in ice cream to create volume and make it smoothy but they dont add air, they make it inhouse and with dairy products. Unfortunately we didnt take the photo.
Taste 5/5
Quantity 5/5
Quality 5/5

They need to improve their fries. Their fries need to be a little more crispy from outside. The size of fries is also not much in length. We found the color a little pale it could be because of warm light. We had a detailed discussion with Owner about the feedback, their practices and little secrets which are part of my review.
Customer Services  5/5
Ambiance 5/5

name: Muhammad Saif
text:
We ordered 1 mutton shinwari karahi, 1 dozen dumba boti (lamb barbeque) and 2 balochi tikkas, raita and salad, 5 drink cans and 7 roghni naans.

Bill: Rs4650

Karahi was good but not as good as the HIGHWAY SHINWARI HOTEL.
Balochi Tikka was too goood.
Dumba boti is THE BEST but still not as good as AL ASIF'S DUMBA BOTI but it was GOOD❤️
Over all a goood place to eat desi food.
There is indoor and outdoor dining option for families.
You will have to wait around 20 mins for the order to be served.

Taste: 7/10
Ambiance (bolay to bethak ka desi mahol) : 8/10

name: Saad Khan
text:
Good atmosphere for outside eating. The food is freshly made and you can pick the cut of meat for your meal. There is at least 30-45 minute wait for the preparation. The naan is traditionally made and refreshed as requested. There is a separate seating option for family and also an inside seating option as well.

The boti seekh with the goat fat is good but must be eaten fresh. The mutton karahi is made to order as requested. The gravy was dry in the karahi. There’s a lot of fat and oil in the good but it tastes better because of it and should be eaten fresh. Leftovers don’t have the same taste.

name: Maaz Bin Khalid
text:
Ah man!! Utter disappointment. Not worthy for another visit.

For context, we ordered the chicken strips and loaded fries for appetisers. For the main, we ordered jalapeño chicken and cheesy Mexican chicken.

The appetisers were great .. decent portion size as well. This hyped us up for the main course which was utter mayhem.

The both chicken dishes had a similar flavour, both were marinated in some sort of desi tandoori masala. This is not what you expect from a restaurant of this level. The lady behind us on the other table complained with the same issue that the chicken was drenched in desi spices and this is not what Mexican chicken flavours are .

name: Mahad Tariq
text:
"Swing" currently has 2 branches in Karachi. I visited the Tariq road branch and it was a pleasant experience. I enjoyed the interior design, seating was nice, and most importantly the dessert was on point. You might have to deal with overcrowding/waiting during the weekends and peak hours. Best bet is to make a reservation if you want to be sure you'll be served.

PS: This is a female friendly environment, so you'll find more women as compared to men here. I didn't mind it tho, even the pink & white theme started to grow on me 

And I almost forgot it's called "Swing" because you can actually sit on one of those swing chairs ️

text:
I recently went to @Tandoor restaurant and invited my family and relatives for iftaar gathering.

I wish I could give it a zero but being a little generous, I rated this restaurant 1/5.
Overall Rating: 1/5
Verdict: Terrible. Waste of time and money.

Despite I booked everything in advance and told them to ensure the right arrangements. It was a disaster right from the very step I took inside the restaurant, to food arrangements, food being tasteless, not being refilled for HOURS, chaos amongst people as lack of management was clearly evident.
Since I was the host and paid a huge amount for the iftar party, I wanted to make sure my guests get a good experience, however below ratings speaks otherwise of how the real Tandoor restaurant is from the inside, how they specialize in ruining events.

Below is my and people whom I invited feedback
•Food variety 1/5
•Staff service speed 1/5
•Food taste 0.5/5
•Food refilling options 1/5
•Space, crowd, food management 0.5/5
•Dining experience 0/5

Overall Rating: 1/5
Verdict: Terrible. Waste of time and money.
If someone asks you to go Tandoor for food or wants to have your opinion on conducting any special event there, just tell them: ABSOLUTELY NOT !

name: Ismail Khan
text:
Ordered maghaz handi, two barbecue platters, chicken corn white and red soup, mutton handi, chicken handi, naan,parathay salads etc for our group of 12 people on a Saturday eve.

Following is the summary of experience

(1) Venue: We walked in to the restaurant around 8:45pm on Sat eve without reservation , we were seated swiftly. We were sitting on the rooftop , while waiting for the order I noticed that although it is Saturday night the place was half empty which was an indication of what was to come. The seating was adequate and staff was friendly. A few birthday parties were being celeberated around us but the noise level was low and we were not interrupted.

(2) Waiting time: Soups were served in 10 min as starters with some nice crackers. White chicken corn soup was bland and missed the mark signifcantly. Red soup was comparatively better and I liked it although there was mixed feedback around the table. The rest of the food was served in around 30min time.

(3) The food: Let's come to the main course, maghaz handi, barbecue platters, karahis and bread.

Barbecue platters had mix of chicken and red meat (not sure it was mutton ,beef or lamb) kebabs and botis and a large chicken tikka piece. Group really liked the chicken tikka but the kebabs and botis were not upto the mark, my beef boti was overcooked ending as hard as rubber. I felt that serving size of barbecue platter did not tally with the price tag and  taste was not at satisfactory level.

I could not really find maghaz in maghaz handi , my father who is a fan of maghaz dishes did not enjoy it that much either as the gravy significantly overpowered any brain flavour and portion in the dish.

I did not try the karahis but the feedback from the table was they were overcooked.

(4) Cost: For a group of 12 people , the bill was around Rs19,500 which in my opinion is on the higher side. I returned to the country after almost 6 years and am used to paying around Rs10,000 for same size groups but inflation and rising costs have unavoidably crept in the dining experience as well.

The group agreed that we may not visit the place again and I will not be recommending Tandoor to anyone.

My rating for various aspects of the experience is as below

- Venue and ambience: 3 out of 5
- Waiting time: 4 out of 5
- Food quantity and taste: 2.5 out of 5
- Staff: 4 out of 5
- Price: 3 out of 5

Overall: 3.3 out of 5

name: Sarmad Zaman
text: Best interior in the area. Wide open sitting space. Very spicy food, I mean really very spicy. After having hot n sour soup, I couldn't feel my tounge. Behari kebabs were very well cooked, but lacking in flavor, chicken seekh kebabs were full of crushed green chilis, beef seekh kebabs were well flavored but a bit raw at the center, chicken handi tasted good, but the chicken were tough and not fresh at all. Brain masala tasted pungent, I really couldn't eat it, mutton Karahi, was cooked to perfection, very juicy and tender, too bad we didn't asked for freshly cooked instead of getting the regular restaurant prehalf cooked version. Chicken Karahi was OK. Chowmen was good. Overall not gona come here again on my expense but surely take an invitation to eat at tandoor. Needs someone to do a serious food taste test here and improve on the usage of spices.

text:
It was great experience with Tandoor. However to ease in our selection their was a guy named Ejaz Hussain who suggestion make our visit more tasteful.
We order chick straps in starter, Chilman biryani and rasjatani kebab selected for main course . Lemon ice to and peach joy was great addition.
Starter taste great and fresh chicken was tender and perfectly coated its goes awesome with its sauce.
Chilman biryani was also mouth watering but a bit dry side you should add raita or chatni and rajastani kebab was really superb kon with paratha
Furthermore, drink playing really vital role in addition of taste, being a desi food lover you definitely enjoy food with quality, quantity and hospitality.

name: Shayan Syed
text:
We were guests at call of my brother in law for family dinner as he came pakistan after a long time and wanted a little get to gather of all big family, I was amazed by the quality of food and staff service level, you guys are nailed almost all so called big names in karachi in same business which others claims to be good but ....!

Tandoor Tean! Keep up the good work and heads of to your kitchen department as I didn't find anything over or under done, and taste of everything ordered was beyond expectation, I am not over excited as I am giving this review after almost ten to twelve days later, if someone really wants to feel good with family dinner outside, this is the best place to feel good in all aspects!

One downer is a little extra pricing, not for me as I know i need to pay little extra for taste, quality and service! So I am very much OK!

One suggestion! ROOF Planters and Plants are very attractive and gives fresh g
Feelings but Please remove artificial plants from main entrance and some other places inside as it gives fake impression, and looks cheap and give strange feeling to see them arround, there are plenty of good options to add in live indoor plants which will enhance extra beauty to your interiors!

Regards,
Shayan Syed

name: Dr Foodie Official
text:
Visited tonight for dinner with friends. Great ambiance , scrumptious food with authentic and delicious taste. This restaurant is a charm for North nazimabad food scene!

Truly an amazing experience.What We ordered was
Garlic Naan (Highly Highly recomended)
The famous and their weekend special Chilman Biryani (showstopper) ❤️
Mushroom Steak (very saucy and delicious) and cheese boti..
Drinks were mint lemonade. It was served with crushed ice (very cool, calming and refreshing)
Presentation was outclass. Service was great. Management was humble.

The place was so crowded today because of weekend but they managed it well and acomodated us without any delay.
You guys must try their Chilman Biryani it is available on weekends.

Overall experience: 9/10
Verdict: Highly recomended for desi cuisine lovers as well as BBQ and Continental.
Must Visit!

name: Fahad Mukhtar
text: You can say, its a Posh version of famous burns road's Malik nihari. It has variety of different versions of nihari from simple to fully loaded. There are many ad-ons that you can try here with nihari. This includes bong, maghaz, nalli. You can have fully loaded nihari at your own risk. They serve it with clean accessories of nihari. If we think about prices, it is slightly expensive but not too much. Dont try their bar BQ, instead, goto Zameer Ansari restaurant, which serves the best bar BQ in Karachi. Also dont get susrprised with the quantity of their desserts. But overall, quality is good. Keep it up.

name: Raza Matin
text:
Malik's is a Karachi dining insitution originally located on the bustling Burns Road in the Sadsar district of Karachi.

The Alamgir Road branch offers much of the same food, including the legendary Nihari, in a far more sanitary and family friendly environment, that is closer to BBQ Tonight than than the ramshackle, restaurant for labourers at it's original location.

This location, managed by one half of the original ownership team, offers a expanded menu, including BBQ, other traditional Pakistani cuisine and Puri Halwa breakfast on weekends.

name: Parwaiz Akhter Ansari
text:
A friend recommended me to have their nihari so visited with my friends. Had special nihari including nulli and maghaz and found it is of unique taste. Price was quite reasonable and taste was not the best, but much better than some other places.

Atmosphere and cleanliness standard is appreciated and far better than other nihari special restaurants like Javed or Zahid etc.

name: Sabih Sahto
text:
One of the best places to have BBQ food in Karachi. The Fry Kebabs are wonderful and so are the Handis and Boneless Karahi. It is best to avoid the newly added Chinese food on their Menu.

I really love the Nihari at Malik's too. However, due to this, the whole restaurant sort of smells like beef and there is a strong Nihari smell in the air often.

The seating arrangement is indoors and there are multiple floors for patrons that come along with their family.

The prices are reasonable and it's overall easy on the pocket. Great value for money. On average, it should be under Rs. 500 per person if you eat in groups.

name: Syed Imran Ahmed (Compuhead)
text: Malik Restaurant is a great addition for traditional food lovers. If you are foodie and like to eat traditional food in a neat, clean and hygenically cooked then Malik Restaurant is the right destination. Staff is supportive. Table service is good. One more thing to remember that payment is paid only through Cash. Although, this can be improved in terms of customer easiness and I believe in future Malik Restaurant management will consider this in future to cater customers. In short, do visit with family for separate sitting and dining arrangements and enjoy quality food in air conditioned, clean and hygenically environment.

But this hotel at Alamgir is not that actually, it's expensive and quantity is also decreased. What you can get at births road is almost half of what you get at Alamgir in the same price. They have also increased menu items and the quality and quantity is so so. I would suggest to have a visit, especially those who have earlier visited Malik Burns Road. Best of luck with the trip

Food was good and meat was properly cooked but the sitting arrangements was not good. They can arrange better but don't know why!
Food was good and we waited long as it was weekend
Price is little bit high if you compare quality and standards as they are providing.
Nearby have many options but koila karahi is available on Bumbai koila karahi. If you want to try food, it ll be great but avoids taking small kids with you.
I m sure you ll like ytge food if u like spoicy food

name: Ali Ather
text: My friend took me there and no doubt it's one of the best karahi in Karachi. We tried their Shahi mutton koyla karahi and chicken koyla karahi. I must say that mutton koyla karahi was awesome as compare to the chicken one. If you are a mutton fan then this place is for you. It's a must try item. The best part is that they have lamb karahi as well and the rates are same for the mutton and lamb karahi. They have sufficient amount of space. They have separate area for families as well. But it's better to sit down at their roof top. They have takhat sitting area on roof top. The space is limited as they have not that huge amount space to accommodate hundreds of people. Their rates are also economical. You can even see their process of making karahi live. Very good experience. Highly recommended for everyone.

Better to go other places.

name: Kashif Abdul Razzaq Misidia
text:
The one of the oldest restaurant of hussainabad food street is quetta Bolan restaurant. It's situated just opp of tayyabi restaurant. If you are planning to visit Hussain abad food street, quetta Bolan will be the best choice for you for traditional & authentic taste of katakat & mutton karhaii with hot warm tandoori roti.
Prices are normal and service is really fast.
You can enjoy the best taste of traditional desi food here. If you are with family than you can enjoy your meal in family hall.

name: Jamal Kherani
text:
It is good restaurant in S.I.T.E. Industrial Area, Karachi. You can't find any other restaurant in that whole area with this good enviornment and so many dishes offering Chinese, Pakistani Food, Continental Food, Sea Food and etc etc.
They have a parking facility also and they also provide security to your cars and bikes.
The staff inside is well manners and well trained just like any other good restaurant you can find inside city.
They have also a conference hall on first floor for the booking of events, meetings and conferences held by any Industrial Company.
The food is awesome but some expensive but it is worthy.
They offer delivery service also to that whole area and if you have a office or a industry in that area and you want to eat good food which is hygiene you can order from them.
It is located on a safe location which is near Police Station and you don't have to fear if you go there for dinner.
They also have other facilities like Gym for ladies and gents. Those people who after working whole day gets free late don't have to worry for going long to other destinations. It is a facility near your Office or Industry.
The best food they have is Pakistani food which is delicious and good in taste. You will love trying this.

name: aqeel ali siddique
text: Went to binoria restaurant after almost 2 decades ( 19 years) ago. Year 2000 when it was inaugurated , this was very well maintained restaurant. Ambience was good and food quality was also good. Now food quality has decreased so much. We ordered half muttton karahi, the qty was very low and it was less in taste what we eat shinwari restaurants near millennium mall. Chicken pulao was not hot , rice were not of long grain. Pulao aroma was no where. Chicken ginger was masala was so so. At last we ordered gajar ka halwa, which was really good. We all (4 ppl) were discussing that we should had only order this halwa. Over all this restaurant has lost its taste. Also traffic around restaurant is very much. U will find difficult for parking.

name: Abdullah Jamal
text:
Pathetic customer service and coordination among staff at reception and staff taking phone orders.

Called and booked a pickup order during Eid holidays owing to restriction of dine in . At the communicated time we reached the outlet and informed the staff at reception about our order. He after 15 minutes and confirming from restaurant informed that no such order is available and if required we have to wait for 60 to 70 minutes.

Based on the communication we decided to head home. After an hour, received a call from restaurant saying that our order is ready for pickup. We informed the caller about our communication with the representative downstairs upon our arrival, but he was insistent to collect the order as he is in no knowledge of the events happening downstairs and even said to put the mobile number on blacklist.

name: Ishaq Bukhari
text:
Located in Bahadurabad, right in front of the famius Alamgir Trust & Mosque is probably the best Kebab House in Karachi (after Waheed Kebab House, Burns road)

Their BBQ variety includes a wide range of mouth watering innovations having unique tastes and recipes.

I got to know about them after watching a food vlogger on Youtube and didn't regret it for a minute.

Totally loved the taste of the 3 different kebabs I ordered and would definitely recommend.

----
The only downside is their staff -- worst douchebaggs ever! Lazyfcks won't even listen to you!

And why make a fancy chubara when guests are to be seated on the road on shittytables??

name: Ibrahim Khan
text:
Went to Zameer Ansari BBQ for its famous BBQ and got a bad experience in return. Starting with the seating area, it was totally disturbing as we got interrupted by panhandlers almost 5 times during our dinner. Coming up to the service, this was the most irritating part; the serving portion was quite small as seen in the pictures below. I’ve took their BBQ home many times and it had never been this less. Secondly, blunders were made in the serving of Parathas twice, claiming to be more than being served. The waiter’s behavior was so rude as if we are eating there for free. Lastly, the calculations in the bill were wrong which we had to double-check. 

Won’t disfavor their food quality which was good as always but the above mentioned issues have made them lose one regular customer.

Most special thing is in this restaurant they have famous desi items in their menu like nargesi koftay , mix sabzi and others. this restaurant also have little parking space besides their restaurant. One more special thing that they have very well mannered servers. This place also offer break fast.

If you are planing to eat some delicious desi and continental food around Hassan Square you can visit this place

name: DIW Newcastle
text:
I have been there once only recently as recommended by my father.

I think I was expecting alot from this place. I personally think that the food was expensive, taste was average and customer service was okay.

I have given 3 star that's me being super lenient towards them. Strictly and openly  speaking they deserve 2 star.

We ordered soup, which was tasteless, chicken seekh kabab and chicken malai boti were of good taste. In addition to that, chicken sashlek and special chicken Chinese were were tasteless as well :( . However, Rogni naan was amazing.

I might not given another chance to them due to the above reasons and also car parking issue.

Hope my comment helps the community out and also the restaurant to work hard on their food.

Thank you :)

2. It's location in Gulshan has now become more popular with people wanting outdoor environment.
3. Still the food quality is good and reasonably priced.

5. Suitable for small gatherings or parties.
6. Parking issues still  persist. Though a parking plot is available.

text: Taste is superb as always. The best thing is that the person who served us food was well-mannered and it seemed he has some training in serving food. He knew everything about the food and ingredients and guided us well. We ordered chicken white handi, malai boti, fish crackers, raita, mix vegetable, plain nan, roghni naan and kashmir nan. Everything was perfect. My husband is sort of vegetarian so mix vegetable was so delighting for him. We tried kasmiri nan for the first time. Our server was from kashmir and when asked about kasmiri nan he guided us so well. We hadnt had authentic pakistani cuisine in years so it was a well worth trip.

text:
The restaurant is clean and tidy when it comes to the dining area. But the furniture is decades old. The ambiance needs to be changed after so many years.
The attitude of the staff and management needs to be a bit humble and professional.
Prices of the food needs to be reviewed since they are on a bit higher side. Speaking of prices, I was shocked when I was charged tax amount extra when I paid for some takeaway food. Which means that there is a difference in payment amount if you pay cash than through your credit card.
Strange.

name: Kashif Abdul Razzaq Misidia
text:
Best #SteamRoastedMutton /lamb in K-Town, and all time favourite restaurant of mine. We use to visit Usmania Restaurant from decades, from my young age.
My favourite dishes there are Mutton steamed Roast, Pulao, #Nargisi-Kofta , fried fish, and Thier  #rainbow-icecream .
Prices here are bit higher than other restaurants, but you can enjoy best Environment and #ambience here.
With ala cart menu, the average expense of Usmania Restaurant is approximately 500 to 700 PKR per pax.
The place is accessible for ♿ wheelchairs and for the people with different disabilities. But still there is a problem of car parking.
But overall I always enjoy my visit there, and recommending to all people who want to spend Thier quality time with their families. That is the best place for them.

#letsguide

name: Asmer Beg
text:
I am an old Grillo customer but their food and service is going down at a fast pace. Today i placed an order (008082/PO), amount Rs.5.549, gave special instruction to keep the chicken spicy. I picked the order and when i came home, opened the order then i found out....2 jalapeno sauces were charged but missing, chicken was dry, 1.5liter drink instead of 1.75liter, diluted sauces, half cooked rice, burgers were wet (they used to put it in box, now they were jsut wrapped in paper). I called the restaurant manager to get owner's contact number for feedback, he said i have to check with owner before giving you the number. Manager then called back saying that owner does not want to talk to you. How ARROGANT!!!!! i am not getting food from this place ever again.

PS: i can share mine and my son's cell number to confirm our history and not a fake customer raising complaint (in case the owner is interested, which i am sure is very busy).

name: sara sheikha
responseFromOwnerText: Thank you so much for your detailed review Ms Sara! We are working harder everyday to provide our customers with the best service
text:
The restaurant is located on main Tariq road which is very congested so it was a task to find parking. We had to park our really far and you know Karachi and that how unsafe it is to walk.
Initially we decided on ordering beef burger, quarter chicken, tiger prawns and fried chicken. But they do not have everything on the menu yet so we ordered another quarter chicken instead of fried chicken. And for tiger prawn the server told us that the prawns are not good and we should not order them.
Khair food came in time and was really tasty. Loved the quarter chicken and beef burger. Although with our order we also got garlic bread and we assumed it was complementary as a lot of restaurants give bread complementary. When the bill arrived we were charged for the bread after talking to them they did remove garlic bread from our bill but told us that we should have asked about it before eating it  may be it was a mistake from both the ends but the guy's tone was way too harsh.
Khair the food is delicious and very reasonable as a single meal is around 450. They need to work on their management though. But they have just started so we can cut them some slack for now.
Food: 5/5
Ambiance: 4/5
Service 3/5

name: Asad Rasheed
responseFromOwnerText:
Thank you for your valuable feedback Mr Asad. We are extremely sorry about this incident and the long waiting time you had to face. We have worked really hard to overcome our shortcomings. It is our top priority to provide our customers with the best service.
We hope that you could give us a second chance. We promise to deliver better service. We will be waiting to read your updated reviews. Hope to welcome you soon Mr Asad.

P.S. We now accept all debit and credit cards

name: Zubair Tareen
text: Today I visited this restaurant first time. Facelift was very impressive & elegant. Restaurant management was so active to welcome every guest by itself. Open air arrangement was spacious & colorful. Ambiance was pleasant. Attending waiters & manager were smart & behaving very well. They’re all in uniform, however, tidiness wasn’t up to the mark. Anyways, their efficiency overshadowed this deficiency. Food delivery time was excellent & all items were freshly cooked. Taste of the food was average up to my standard( May be excellent for others). Tempora prawn was over-cooked & karahi was over spicy for me( May be normal for others). Overall food quality, quantity & serving style was good. Another appreciable thing that the manager himself visited our table to ask about our opinion. Waiter Hisham was also very active in serving our table. My visit to this place was a refreshing one & I’d like to visit them again.

name: Dr. Manzoor Hussain Memon
text:
Good place,  good environment,  good food,  quality service. These are attributes of Haveli Kebab & Grill Restaurant. However,  there is a room for improvement in food as well as environment.  Food can be improved by quality cooks while environment can be improved further by adding some antique things and wall images and colors.

Overall a good place to visit for food. Located on a so called food street,  where you can find lots of other restaurants.  One speciality of the restaurant is parking convenience, Wallet parking service is also there.

name: dryousuf yak
text: Went their a few days back, when I was in khi. Courteous staffs, average ambience with rooftop sitting and floor sitting on ground level. We ordered in recommendation of the server...shahi karahi beef, and some chicken handi also. Rest we ordered katakat, their speciality of the day Mughlai tikka (leg piece stuffed with minced meat), kasturi boti and last, zafrani and one other flavoured kulfi. For startes had hot/sour soup. The soup by far was excellent and one bowl enough for two. Shahi karahi was good but nothing out of extraordinary. Chicken handi, average taste. Kasturi boti should have been labelled as fustuq (Arabic for pistachio) and was missing taste and flavour and in menu it said with cheese topping but was served without it. When asked, the reply was: chef changed and new chef don't serve with cheese! Mughlai tikka ok. Katakat was also average and don't know why they ground it so much that everything just become one ?gooey ?sludge thing. Second best was Zafrani kulfi.....too good. Pricy and exclusive of 13% tax. No Wi-Fi and parking can be an issue. Score 6-7/10. Good but not extraordinary in terms of taste and flavour.

Food, taste and quality is pretty good.

name: Vasif Abbas
text:
✔️Visited for the first time so had to go for safer order options, ordered the BBQ platter with rice. Checked out their hummus as the appetizer, was not disappointed. Have not had such fantastic hummus in a while, much better than those who claim to be authentic ones out there.

✔️For the main course: have to admit, this was the best BBQ I've had in a while, the bites were juicy, taste was excellent and scent was fantastic. A real treat for a meat lover like myself. The rice was rich and fresh too.

✔️Thou, I was expecting a more oriental Turkish vibe, but it was just a contemporary restaurant feel that you'd get in most eateries of Karachi.

✔️The music was a bit loud too, given we were there before the actual rush hour, so it might not feel that loud when the place is packed.

✅ Get there before 8 pm to avoid the usual rush and waiting times on a weekend night. And keep cash along with. Payment via cards isn't available.

name: Jamil Abbasi
text:
(Translated by Google) When we arrived at 10:30 pm, there was still a small crowd of people waiting. We were seated in a waiting area, which was not inappropriate. Twenty minutes later we got the table. We ordered Hummus and Family Platter for the meal. Family Platter Chicken Adna Kebab, Mutton Zira Kebab, Antakya Chicken Kebab, Mutton Adna Kebab, Mutton Arfa Kebab, Shish Tok, Istanbul Tekka, Mutton Turkish Tekka, Mutton Enigol Kofta, Girl Wings, chicken chops and mutton kabsa (by the way, chicken kabsa is in the family platter but you can make mutton kabsa by paying extra). The food was good. Mutton kabsa in particular was excellent. The rubbish in it was even better than Mutton rubbish from Barbecue Tonight. The amount of hummus was enough for six of us. The bread with hummus was delicious. It was quite different and good from Peta Bread. Overall, the Olive Restaurant offers excellent Turkish food, which is admirable in taste and flavor.

text: Went there with a group, it was a nice experience. They do a good effort to serve Turkish cuisine. We ordered big fire grill, cold meze, kabsa rice with lamb & spicy chicken, and few more items. Overall the food was nice, and well presented. I particularly like mandi rice, chicken chops, sizzling kebab, Turkish bread and kunafa with cream. But some grill items are a bit too spicy for Turkish cuisine. I think menu should have spicy rating and option to offer low/no chilli versions. I know most desi like chilli but then are who want to enjoy the a different cuisine as close to authentic as possible. It was a busy evening and service was a little lost at times, but the food made up for it.

name: Sameer
text:
1. Expect a long wait outside if you don't have a reservation. They don't let people inside if they don't have a table which is a good thing because no one wants hungry customers towering over your table while you eat your meal.
2. Staff is curteous, well mannered and deserve a good tip.
3. Starters come fairly quickly. Hummus needs a little improvement, a little more lemon and garlic should do the trick, however the consistency and texture is great. The zaater blend used is a bit bland. The bread is fantastic as Turkish bread should be.
4. The kebabs are cooked to perfection. The mutton and chicken sizzler is nice, however I expected them to not be cut up kebabs on hot plates.
5. Brings lots of cash. They don't accept debit or credit cards.

name: Sheikh Rameen Usmani
text:
It was my best decision to been there on a working day around 6pm. The place was so calm to spent a quality time and enjoy your meal as not too much hustling was there to irritate you at that time. We were 2 girls who easily got our seats simply walking-in. Now comes to the order we made☺️ After a thorough study of menu card, as everything was so appealing, we have ordered for chicken kabsa (spicy), sizzling mutton kebab, lemon mint glacier and another drink( I don't remember the name) and kunafa ( the show stopper).
The taste was awesome the rice, the chicken everything was perfectly cooked, they have also given a cute naan with kababs. The raita and chutney were love to eat with every bite of kebabs the size of kunafa was bigger than usual ones, the ambiance is so soothing.
It was my first and the best experience. We have ordered more than appetite of 2 girls, so yes we asked them to parcel our leftover food.
Total damage: around 3,890 including taxes. But believe me it's worth trying for once at least if anyone find it expensive. Just give it a chance guys.

Recently Visited zeytin on wife's♥️ recommendation
To try some Turkish cuisine
From the First impression the ambiance was pleasant and welcoming
Everything was perfectly organized ,Now if we talk about food we ordered Mutton Cop Sis(chutney was too good also got re-fill),Small Bbq platter which includes mutton adana kebab ,chicken adana kebab ,shish taduk and mutton turkish tikka with grill wings(platter was enough for 2 person and has mostly all bbq item on menu card) ...flavours were upto the mark neither bland nor too spicy , In dessert they served freshly made Kunafa for us which was cheesy  and creamy and every bite of it was to die for✨
Staff was friendly and cooperative 
Inshallah Will visit again soon

name: Bilal Kamran
text:
I'm normally not a fan of Turkish or Arab cuisines, but I absolutely loved their take on Turkish food! Undoubtedly the best food I had on my recent Khi visit.

- Mixed Grill platter (small): no fancy words needed. All kababs on it taste amazing. Mutton adana, chicken adana, shish touk, kusbasi mutton, grilled wings. Came with a decent portion of rice, which alone was quite aromatic and flavorsome. 10/10.

- Sizzling Mutton kabab: delicious, my family rated it 9/10 but I'll rate it 7/10. Three marks off for drowning it in butter. I know that's how they normally serve it in Turkey, but I don't like my food drenched in an oilfield.

- Chicken Shawarma pide: The Turkish crust is good and different, but the center topping is any standard pizza you get at Pizza Max/California Pizza etc. I thought it would be a good starter, but one serving is too small for 4 people (serves max 2 imo). 5/10.

- Kunafa: Best in town. I don't care how many people can eat in one serving, I'll order 10 and eat them all alone. 10/10.

Conclusion: food is great, service is decent. Zeytin is amazing, and luckily it's on the best side of the bridge. 9/10.

text:
I was very excited to visit Zeytin but a bit disappointment i faced that ut is not according to the hype created in market.
I tried chicken khabsa, chivken shawarma pide and Masala sizzling kebab
Khabsa was average which can available at many other places and its chicken taste was not so good
Chicken shawarma pide was not upto mark and will not recommend it as its bread is tasteless and cheese topping was also nit much to taste it properly.
Masla sizzling kebab was awesome in taste and thats the only thing which we like most but not served sizzling but its ok, but if any one dont like oily dishes than dont try it.
Service was average and they did not serve food properly ina manner that other persons get order before us but they came after us and they serve us shawarma pide first which disappoint us and then we have to wait for remaining order, than they serve khabsa and then after 8 minutes they serve sizzling kebab which should placed first bcz sizzling kebab can enjoy only when it is hot.
I will not recommend anyone to came here specially, if you are nearby then you can try it.

name: Ali Shamim
text:
Zeytin has definitely exceeded our expectations when it comes to food quality and taste. Thankfully they didn't cater the typical Turkish flavor which most won't appreciate. Recommended for fine dining experience.

The ambience could use better lighting and a touch of Turkish signature elements. The Kebabs were served on a wooden platter which was not wide enough and the whole Seekh couldn't fit and ended up dangling at both ends.

We specially liked the Kabsa (not Turkish), it contained beautifully grilled chicken meat on the bed of aromatic and flavorful rice.

Turkish Adana kebab was perfectly cooked... Juicy and tender. Really loved them. I don't know why they included Wings in the platter... Maybe to justify the price of the platter.

The food was pricey but the overall experience was worth it.

Their delivery menu does not qualify as good..I had ordered one family platter and one fire platter as advised by the waiter on phone for 12 people..
When it arrived the food was not only cold it lacked most of the dishes described on the platters..it had few adana kebabs about 2 in each of the platters and was mostly filled with cut  chicken pieces..they had no mutton in either of the platters and no salad or pickles.
Humous was also missing from the order
ON top of it the waiter did not present any receipt but was given the full amount 14000 plus tip.
When I raised this issue to the management no action was taken whatsoever..As a result they blocked my number.

Conclusion is avoid ordering from zeytin from their delivery menu.

name: Muhammad Usman
text:
Let's start with ambience! It was good. Lively. Colourful. Though tbh as we sat in the lower level, it got darker. Tbh I don't get the trend where the higher end the place, the darker the ambience but that's just me ig.

Service! It was top notch. They were very patient and accommodating. Let's just say they deserved a very good tip. Which they got.

Food! The thing you're slogging through this review for! Turkish food! Because this was a Turkish place. Apparently. Food was... Cliché. Which isn't a reflection on the quality of the food itself. It was tasty, hot, brilliantly cooked, in good quantity and I genuinely liked the food. But for a Turkish place with Turkish food, I expected... More. But that's just my personal reflection on it I suppose. Of the Kebab, the Kabsa (is that what they called it? I don't remember) and the Peri peri pizza, I liked the pizza the most, which can either be a reflection of my puny taste buds or it can be a reflection on the clichéness of the food. That's for you to decide I suppose.

Price! For a place that looked good and felt good, it was rather economical. Not the cheapest of places but 4 people ate (though it was rather modestly) and the bill came out to just above 3,000Rs. It was decent.

Overall, 8/10. Would visit again.

I wish I could say that these pictures do justice to the sublime authentic finger licking food that was at Zeytin. I was forced to ask the manager about the chef's roots because I was certain that he wasn't from around and I was right, the head chef is Turkish, home to some of the greatest skewered meat. Nonetheless, he knew his was into the middle eastern heritage of lebanese cuisine. Because, everything, from the hummus, shawarma platter, the bbq platter and the aromatic rice that was steaming till the very end. The team certainly deserves a round of applause and the food is as authentic as it could be.
For more reviews, please follow @the_ktown_man on instagram.

name: Sarrah Shabbir
text:
We visited on a weekday and the place was super crowded. We had to wait for an hour before we got our table. It was totally worth the wait.

We ordered Chicken Kabsa and Sizzling kebabs with Mint Mojito and Saudi Champagne.
The food arrived in less than 10 minutes. Sizzling kebabs were served with Turkish bread which is melt-in-your mouth soft. The kebabs were juicy, succulent and served with veggies.
The Spicy Chicken Kabsa was a total hit. The rice were extremely flavorful with the right combination of all the spices. The Spicy Chicken on top was juicy and tender with a slight tanginess that added more to its flavorful.
Drinks were good too.

The service was extraordinary.

name: Syed M. Ayaz
text:
Been a huge fan of their shawarma wraps. In fact I used to recommend everyone I know to prefer it over any other shawarma in the vicinity.
Unfortunately they have downgraded it and reduced its size to a quarter shorter and also compromised the quantity of stuffing in it too.
It's not that their business is running low. Masha Allah they are doing great its almost an hour long waiting house full affair most of the time. Weekends traffic and parking outside show they are doing well but saddened to see how in such good times they are compromising on their quality of service.
Alas! I guess, this is typically the same mundane cycle by which any business goes downwards.

text:
Well, here is my experience I'd like to share. I planned an evening for my husband on his bday. I wanted to pre plan everything so I called zeytin, and the person who dealth with me till the end I'm sorry I couldn't understand your name properly but may be it was 'Jazvi', a gentleman who gave me good suggestions, helped me execute my plan perfectly as I wished. And when my husband reached there they served him so nicely, wished him made him feel special. Food was just outstanding. So unique such a flavourful balanced taste of lebanese cuisine.
Ordered chilli bites in starters, kunaafa as in bday cake, chk shawarma pide, tepsi kabab, istanbul tikka and everything was upto a class!! Served hot wirh perfect timings as requested.

I highly recommend lebanese food lovers, and also ppl to try it once it's worth it. You'd love the taste bcz it has that Pakistani touch and it makes it just right!

name: Muhammad Alee
text: Lovely experience! Will go again for sure the food taste is on point! The original Turkish preps and the taste was outstanding chef have curated the recipes in a way you will love everything! The ambiance was classy dim lights and traditional turkish music playing will make you feel like you're in anatolian eatery. I ordered family platter and it had all their bbq items on a single wooden board! From kebabs to wings to meat pieces everything was made in butter and the meat was tasty and juicy! Unlike our traditional bbq which is dry and too much spicy. The restaurant have justified its theme taste and quality highly highly recommended 10/10 ratings. I will go again for sure to try more items on their menu!

name: Umer Abdul Rauf
text:
Suddenly ended up here after wife's advice.....
It was something special!.... Never had Turkish food but this place is amazing .
I went here on Sunday it was very crowded waiting for around 1 hour but as we were 2 so got seating immediately.
If we talk about Ambience it was good seating area is large both on ground floor and basement.
Staff is cooperative and helpful.

If we talk about food it was simply mouthwatering, I ordered 2 dishes:
-Sizzling Mutton Kebab
-Shish Touk

Sizzling Kebab was super yummy it was my first experience of this type of dish served with fried onions and chillies and also served with Turkish bread
Shish Touk was also tasty, it was dry and spicy

Both the dish was very well served and one amazing thing is service was super fast

My final word is highly recommended!

text:
Sometimes the places actual experience surpasses the expectations but unfortunately this was not one of those occasions. Food was just good not exceptional.
Valet service outside was pathetically slow.
Food Service was good and I must say exceptionally fast. They serve Turkish and Arabic food.
Hummus was ordinary, Pide (sort of Turkish Pizza) was bland, Sizzling mutton kabab had less kababs and loads of vegetables.
The only dish that we enjoyed was Mixed grill platter .
May be its not the restaurant, since it was our first visit we made wrong choices of food.
Next time if we go, we will order only the dry kababs alongwith fattoush salad.
Bill of 4 people came out to be 4,750 with just a large water bottle and no other drinks or desserts.  They take cash 9nly. NO CARDS.

name: imran amin
text: I recently visited Turkey and had experienced cuisine of different kinds. When I heard about this Zeytin, I brought into my mind some expectations. The ambience is good, it is a big place with tables kept on the ground floor and basement. The waiters were very friendly and the supporting staff was very very active. Initially it seemed that they had some over sized staff, but the good service justified my concern. I ordered PIDE and beef shawarma from the Iskandar kebap menu. Initially was served with Pide which was very very very fresh. The dough was  so fresh and mouth melting that even if there would not be any filling I would have still eaten it easily. The beef Shawarma was also served which I ate and the beef taste was almost exactly the same as I found in turkey. The manager informed us that the head chef if this restaurant was a Turkish and which is why the food tastes like Turkish. The meat is very fresh and is bought on daily basis with a same day return policy. The manager was kind enough to serve us with Turkish coffee with milk which I also enjoyed. I was full so I could not order the Kunafe which I am planning to order when I visit the place again. A very good restaurant to visit again. Parking is difficult though but the restaurant has valet services.

name: Hamza Yousuf
text:
New turkish place. Apparently owned and managed by the same people who run Mandi House just a few hundred meters down Shaheed-e-Millat.

I live close by, so I've seen it pretty crowded over the weekends. Made up my mind to visit on a weekday. Went today (Monday) at around 9PM, and there were maybe 4 tables full; the rest were all available.

Service was pretty quick, and on point. The menu is decent. They've apparently added some new dishes, which you'll notice once you look at the menu. Serving staff is well trained, although they could use a little more training in terms of menu expertise. Our serving staff had a hard time suggesting what we should order; can forgive that, though, since the restaurant is pretty new so I suppose it'll take a while before they're well versed with the menu.

We ordered hummus as a starter, and chicken shawarma platter, chicken adana kabab, and sizzling kabab (chicken).

The hummus is nothing to write home about. Pretty standard hummus, a little bland; would have preferred it to be a little more tangy. Not like the hummus you'd find in the middle east.

The adana kabab, again, is bland, but that is to be expected. Cooked well, tasted decent. Sizzling kabab was comparatively spicy, so I'm glad we ordered those 2.

The start of the day, however, was the shawarma platter. If there's one thing Zeytin can do to utter perfection, it's the shawarma. I have yet to taste shawarma that's so close to the authentic shawarma you find in the middle east; their shawarma is perhaps the only reason they get a 5 star rating from me.

Serving sizes are quite decent. Pricing is on the higher side, but unlike some of the other rip-off turkish/middle east themed restaurants in Karachi (I'm looking at you, Baituti!), they don't skimp on serving size.

Overall, definitely worth trying out. I'll be coming back for that shawarma a few more times!

text: Okay so we went there yesterday all excited to try turkish flavors. Environment was excellent, waiters seemed a bit untrained and uninformative about dishes. As it is an introductory cuisine, servers should have been more helpful and able to guide through the menu. But that wasnt the case. On top of that, 2 of our orders came up wrong. We ordered cheese pide, half way through it, n i realised there were chicken pieces in between. So the. Waiter took it back to replace. Next was the pizza, we ordered shawarma flavor n wat came was no where near shawarma flavor. We didnt bother replacing it though. But seriously disappointed. It took away our trust in the 1st place on our 1st visit. The 3rd dish we had ordered was sizzling kebab.. We were in doubt all the way to end if that was actually wat we ordered or it got mixed up too. In short, poor kitchen coordination. The food was okay. 3.5 out of 5 for that. Do give it a try. Soup was excellent but very less in quantity.

text: So my wife decided to give me treat on my birthday. As we were passing by Khalid Bin Waleed road deciding the destination, we saw this new eatery at corner of intersection and instantly decided to try it today. As we entered the restaurant, we were amused by the interior decoration and detailing being done by the Architect. We were warmly greeted and seated by the staff and given menu book to choose our delicacies. To our surprise, the restaurant had complete Turkish cuisine items from Adina Kebab to Shawarma and Pide. We ordered Kiyamali Pide, Mix Grilled Platter (small) and Fattoush Salad. My oh my, the taste was ginger licking good! They have Turkish Head Chef who really knows about his cuisine and it's flavours. Our night was well spent, and we hope to visit this restaurant often.

name: SYED MUHAMMAD IBRAHIM
text:
If you are from Middle Eastern countries and craving for some authenctic Arabic mandi than this is the place for you.

From service to food everything is amazing.

Had a very soothing yakhni in the starter. It is a blessing in the start of winters in Karachi.

Had Hummus as well in the starter along with freshly made pita bread. Too good and very lite.

Had Mutton Madbee in the main course. The spice level of this dish is great for Karachi people but if you want that Arabic taste go for MANDI. The mutton was very tasty, juicy and tender. Quality of rice was amazing.

Lemon Mint Glacier was the drink which was really good.

The staff was cooperative and attentive.

Loved it! ♥️

name: Majid Khalid
text:
As always, I will try to be as honest as possible with my review.

Good Things

1. Nice taste
2. Nice service
3. Nice ambiance
4. Clean toilets
5. Nice environment (ideal for families)

Bad Things

1. Quantity of rice with madfoon or mandi (yes they bring more but it's still not enough. Also the way it is laid out in such a thin layer is off putting)
2. Table size. There is not enough space for stuff
3. Seating (the seats are a bit deep and low making it hard to reach the dish and cutlery. Very discomforting)
4. PRICEY (Mutton Madfoon for 2 costs 3100 and on top of that you have 13% GST)

Wasn't a bad experience but wont go back. It is not worth the price.

There are not any outside space for sitting. They have sitting options on tables as well as floor. I preferred to sit on floor in cubicle. We ordered two variety of mandi. The food quality and service was excellent but i was not happy with their prices. They have different type of mutton and chicken mandi also have kunafa. The prices was very high but i'll definitely go again.

We had dinner on 1st Feb, 2020 at this restaurant and had mutton madfoon, and another mutton dish alongside 2 servings of arabic salad.

Firstly, I must say the service is very quick. Although waiters are always howering over you so better not go on Friday and Saturday nights. Food is ok but not very good as I was expecting from it. Pricing is very expensive - as is trend for such joints. Double mutton mudfoon cost 2200/platter and for 4 it cost a woophing Rs.5100 - a price which is not worth it despite meat being very tenderly cooked.

I requested them to meet their Yemeni chef but they refused point black.

We did not try out their kunafa because we were full. For 7 adults and 2 kids the bill was Rs.12000.

Verdict:  Recommended if you have extra cash to spare because like other Mandi restaurants it does not really value add to your life. And in a country like Pakistan it is not worth to have such expensive meals.

It was a great experince and worth to try

text: Table service available, We asked to be seated on the floor but were told it's only available for groups. A very busy restaurant at weekends. Mutton was tender and rice spicy for authentic Mandi. Was amazed to see most people using utensils to eat the rice which is supposed to be enjoyed with hands. Drinks like Mojitos were served in plastic containers and drinks section is extremely limited. Other wise as expected as to regular Mandi restaurant which has cropped across Pakistan. Must mention the staff who were very friendly and made us feel extremely comfortable even when seated in a high traffic zone.

Plus there's a horrendous construction going on right in front of the restaurant. Lighting was also very dim in the service road outside of the restaurant. The price of the food was also a bit on the higher side in my opinion. Al Ridan has similar menu, similar service level, better location and slightly lower prices. However, I do admit that Mandi house does have better interior/ambiance.

Overall good experience. Would definitely go again.

text:
The taste is delicious to the core! Man o man! I tried Ridaan earlier but this is another level. This doesn't mean Ridaan quality has gone down, but Mandi House taste can't be compared. The rice are filled with flavor. In my personal opinion, Mandi House taste is more authentic compared to Ridaan's.  Sitting arrangement is slightly better and clean compared to Ridaan. Highly recommend to try the Mutton/Chicken Madfoon. My favorite was Ridaan till I tried Mandi House! It's currently the best in town...  Hummus is no where near the hummus we get to taste in the Middle East.

Kanafeh is also spot on! A must try for everyone!

name: Ali Siddiqui
text:
Delicious. Eaten mutton madfoon and kunafa. The kunafa in picture, outside it cream (milk pak cream) and inside kunafa is cheese (enough for 3 person) as it heavy.

Rice is infused with green cardamon and light flavour. The mutton is good, black marination and meat is easily falls of the bone.

Do try, it great for family. This mutton is not spicy, best for non spicy lovers.

The mutton ordered is single serving, and once rice is finished, it can be reordered again for free (unlimited).

name: M.Hammad Bhojani
text:
A good place for families very specious.
We were 5 friends and we ordered 3 Mutton Madfoon and 1 chicken Madbi on recommendation of ordering boy, which was too much and we were unable to finish the chicken madbi.
Mutton madfoon was delicious and meat was very well cooked. Though it was not spicy at all.
Rice quality was ok, I liked the taste of Ridan Mandi more than their rice.
We also tried their Kunafa and Basbossa. Kunafa is a must try for everyone but Basbossa is not recommended as it was too dry.
Also they don’t accept Cards for payment only cash payment which is a negative point and we were not aware of this until we got the bill.

name: sara saadi
text:
The exterior of the place is good. When you step inside, its exotic... eastern and western blends of seating and decor renders the place almost heavenly. The reception and waiting area are at the ground floor while the seating arrangement is in the basement. It is furthur divided into two seating styles... the conventional table-chair seating and the traditional floor seating in separate cubicles.
The food is really good if you are a fan of arabic food. It has a diverse arabic menu and all dishes are mouth wayering and well presented. An excellent experience!

name: Zeeshan Ahmed Sheikh
text: I totally recommend this place. I got excellent service, we were a party of 5 people and we had a server who was super attentive and always coming back to check on us and ask us if we needed anything. We also had a visit by the manager or owner not sure, but he was super humble and he offered us a complimentary dessert that wasnt available to all customers , he sat with us for a good 30 minutes or so and collected feedback and shared his experiences and challenges they face. Mastering authentic middle eastern food isnt easy, we pointed out flaws and how they could improve the dishes that we ordered - i'd like to point out that the food was amazingly good however, since my guests were from middle east they had a better idea on the how the food should be. Overall my guests were satisfied by the food, quality of service and the respect shown by the restaurant handler.

name: Muhammad Hashir Fazal
text:
Huge shout out to @mandihouseofficial for their hospitality and amazing service specially their owner and upper management it was good to be at Mandi House. On their recommendation we ordered Mutton Madfoon Mandi (Mutton Buried in ground and cooked under natural heat) served with Rice it was amazing perfectly tendered soft juicy mutton pieces. I have always criticized Mandi vendors that rice are dry but this wasn't the case this time. We were two so we ordered Single plate as you can get free refill of Rice. We ordered fries too and they crispy and crunchy. For drink we ordered Lemmonade and it was one of the best I have ever had. Bravo Mandi House.
I consider Mandi House to be best Mandi vendor if we talk about Ambience, Taste and Service.
5 ⭐ 
#follow @myfoodietummy my Instagram account for more reviews ♥️

name: Kashif Abdul Razzaq Misidia
text:
MANDI HOUSE, KARACHI.

It was grand opened on 11th Nov. We visited it on 12th.
The interior is very beautiful. It feels like you're in Arabia. Mandi House tried their level best to make a Replica of Saudia's Mandi houses.

There were both Carpet and Table sitting. We wanted to try the carpet one so they made us wait for 10 minutes.

The staff was highly courteous. Ambiance was great. Environment was very good.

They were also offering refill of rice.

Coming to the food, We ordered 1 Chicken Mandi and 1 Mutton with Kunafa as dessert.

●Chicken Mandi: Taste=8.78/10
Chicken was very, I said very, well marinated and tasty. Rice were ordinary. Use of sauces made the rice and chicken delicious!
Single: 600
Double: 1200
For 4: 2200

●Mutton Mandi= 7.65/10
Mutton was very tender, well cooked. Had its own original taste. I felt usage of some spices as on chicken would have been great.
Rice were mainly the same. A must try if you love mutton!
Single: 1150
Double: 2300
For 4 : 4400

●Kunafa= Taste: 9.8/10
A dessert that takes you to another world. Creamy vermicelli. Rich flavour. Highly recommended.
Price: Rs 450

Overall rating: 9.8/10

: Taste, Ambiance, Environment, Service.
: Price were a bit high.

We also got 15% opening discount on our bill. :)

name: Rahemah Mahmud
text:
Loved the entire experience. From the beautiful decor to the comfortably plush seating (we choose to sit in the cubicles on the floor - there are also tables for those who prefer it) all the way to the courteous staff and of course the absolutely delicious food, everything was pretty great.

The seating was super comfortable. The carpets are super soft and plush, the pillows make for a very relaxed eating environment. You can literally chill out and enjoy your food.

We ordered the hummus for starters followed directly by the main course. The hummus was fantastic. One of the better ones in the city for sure. The chicken mandi was perfectly cooked; the rice so flavorful and the chicken so soft and succulent it was literally melting in the mouth.

The mint yogurt and the spicy tomato salsa/chutney were the perfect condiments to accompany the Mandi.

For dessert we had the signature Kunafe. Just YUM. I have no words to describe how good it was.

Though there were a variety of dishes and drinks on the menu we choose to stick to the very basics and boy am i glad we did.
The food is absolutely filling but not overpowering or heavy. The rice in the mandi dish can be re-filled on demand if need be though we found the servings more than enough (but we are a family of 6 with modest appetites). So for us, 2 mandi dishes were more than enough (one dish is said to serve 2). We also just ordered and shared one serving of the dessert. Its yum but it is pretty heavy so you really cannot eat more than a couple of bites.

The value for money especially given the ambiance, the decor, and the flavor of the eatery is exceptional. Our total bill for 6 people was less than 4.5k.

Another point to note is the attention to cleanliness at the restaurant. Each cubile was lined with a plastic sheet sort of like a table runner for the food and plates to be kept on. It was very efficient to just wrap the sheet to catch any and all food spillage once we were done eating. As soon as we finished a very neat and clean server came and quickly cleaned up the place, replaced the table runner and presented us with the dessert not even 5 minutes after we ordered it though we were told it usually takes 10+ minutes for it to arrive.

Highly recommended - will certainly visit again( for the food and for the pictures) i was only able to take the pictures of the dessert because none of us could wait before we dove into the food - the fragrant smells were just that compelling. If nothing else that should tempt you into paying a visit.

For a newbie startup (it opened its doors to the public less than 10 days ago) the management has done a fantastic job. I hope they can keep it up in the future. Consistency is key!

name: Arc Tempest
text:
Yesterday, I visited the restaurant, ordered and received food (steak, chicken corn soup, chocolate cake), ate steak and soup at home first, and opened the package to eat cake for dessert, and two live cockroach cubs popped out of one of the two cakes.

Last time, I had a meal in a restaurant with my family, and at that time, the hair of the kitchen chef was mixed in Massed Potato, the side menu of the steak that my mother was eating.

The taste of this restaurant's food is not bad, but its hygiene is the worst restaurant I've ever visited. I also visited two Kababjees at different branches, but it was okay there.

I don't recommend this restaurant. If you want to go, I recommend going to another branch, Kababjees.

name: Naeem Ashraf
text:
Recently I had a debacle when I ordered Kababjees through FoodPanda. So, today I decided to order directly through Kababjees. Hoping that it was FoodPanda which had issues....But that does not seem the case.

I placed an order around 7:45 PM, which I was conveyed to receive in next 65 minutes max. After 50 minutes of placing order, I call them back to know about my order. Because Rider usually calls u by then to confirm the delivery address. But each time I called, they said rider will be reaching me in 10 to 15 minutes.

On 4th call after 1.75 hours (9:30 PM), their agent shocked me by saying that order was placed just 50 minutes ago on 8:40 PM; not 7:45 PM...WTH!

Meanwhile, I started updating them with this situation on their WhatsApp complain number. But they did not bother to respond.

Miraculously, rider came after 2 hours and 10 minutes. When I asked why he got late, he said, he received order 30 minutes ago.

I don't know who is lying: rider or the kababjees agent. Because order slip says order was made around 7:45 PM.

On top of this misery, even the Malai Boti that I order, seems to have less quantity and was cold. I already suffered enough, so decided to eat it anyway; because I could not waste another 2 hours on replacement order, due to their sheer incompetence.

I am attaching the screen shots of the messages that I send to their whatsapp complain number.

name: Usama Ansari
text:
I think Kababjees is the ultimate stop for something for everyone. From stakes, Chinese, to Pakistani and continental cuisines. I've had experience of celebrating my son's birthday at their North branch and later a dine-out at Shaheed-e-Millat's.

On both occasions, customer service was one to marvel at. To me, customer service is of utmost importance. I'm aware it's pricey but if you've the dough, you can't go wrong with Kababjees cuisines.

Peshawari Karahi is the winner for me. On the sweet side (Kababjees Bakers), their Red Velvet cake is the way to go!
