name: J o k e r YT
Ahsan Zahid
text:
This place is very well-designed (Masha-Allah) and was nearly empty when we arrived for dinner at 7:45 PM on a Tuesday evening.

We were promptly seated as I headed for the restroom to wash-up for dinner. I was pleased to find that the washroom facilities were very clean and odor-free.

The best experience of the entire night was the outstanding service we were given. The young server was incredibly courteous, friendly, and helpful. If not for his amazing work, we wouldn't have enjoyed the experience as much.

The food was just OK. I did not find the Kababs very flavorful and the masala chops were very small with almost no meat on the bone. The dhaga kabab was likely the best of the kabas we sampled. Likewise, the behari boti was pretty good, but nothing special.

If not for the incredible service, I'd give this restaurant two or three stars solely on the taste of the food.

name: Aurangzeb “AGzee” Durrani
text: We ordered Chicken Corn Soup, Chicken Peshawari Karahi, Seekh Kabab and Chicken Malai Boti along with chapati, roghni naan and garlic naan. The food was good but their Garlic Naan were a big let down. They were like a bread and had no taste of garlic or butter. Upon informing the management they provided us with a fresh Garlic Naan which was better than before. But again their naan had bread-like taste which didn't compliment the taste of the Karahi and BBQ. Plus, due to the temperature inside the naans went cold real fast. The service however was good. One more thing that I would like to highlight is that they do not have family bowls or family serving for soups. They only have single serving for Hot & Sour and Chicken Corn Soups. Plus, they don't serve crackers with the soup. However, they did serve us with Garlic Bread while we were waiting for our order to be served. All in all, Kababjees Shaheed-e-Millat Road has a good ambiance, better service and decent food taste. But honestly, I didn't find it as good as Kababjees Do Darya. I would recommend it for family gatherings and dining out and if you have HBL Credit Card then you can enjoy good discounts as well.

text: Fast excellent service. Good ambiance. Big place can accommodate large number of customers. Big menu has almost everything from fast food to Bbq to Chinese to karahe, handi. But the price to quantity / serving size were very disappointing. Price does not justify the quantity served. Ordered masala fries for 225 but what we got, in terms of quantity would be available for less then 50 in other places. Apart from that taste of Mutton peshawari Karahi, Chullu kabab was good. Will only recommend if serving size gets better. Also many  discounts are available which may reduce customer disappointment a bit but still they need to reassess their serving size.

name: Bashshar Atif
text: Kababjees was a world class experience. The employees were active and freindly and did thier best to meet our needs and exceed our expectations. Everything from the valet parking to the ambience of the restrant was superb. The washrooms were clean and so was the dining area. I ordered the Kebab platter, Lamb Chops, Cheese Naan and the Chicken Nihari. Out of all of these dishes the Nihari, kebabs, and lamb chops were the greatest. I have eaten these foods around the world and in many local restaurants but the taste and quality does not even come close to the likes of Kababjees. If you are in Karachi, you must try this exquisite restaurant.

text:
Extremely bad customer service at this branch of Kababjees. Serving size at this branch differs a lot from the other ones. Waiters too not only stare at ladies inappropriately, but are even found eve-teasing at times.

You order paneer reshmi handi here & it is barely filling for two persons at this outlet, unlike the other ones where it is quite easily fillling for 3 persons. Fish is over-fried (burnt) and they don't care about complaints. All in all a very unwelcoming environment.
This branch is HIGHLY not recommended.

name: Haziq Akhtar
text:
As always and as in every branch of kababjees they have just excellent authentic Pakistani food. They don't shy away from using necessary spices in the name of so called "catering for the masses". They purely believe in real taste and their ingredients truly feel fresh (only good knows if this true, i will not vouch for anyone's freshness after watching so many horrible videos from Pakistan).

To sum it up, Kababjees is one of my top choice for desi dine out with my family. Apart from desi, even their chicken chow mein was super delucious (again desi style chow mein, not authentic chinese).
